c)	The Municipal Accountant exert effort to trace back prior years’ records and identify the unidentified balances of CIP accounts amounting to P5.883 million and Land Improvements amounting to P97,163.40;

d)	The Management obtain records/documents pertaining to the acquisition of the unrecorded parcels of land with total market value of P5.606 million and direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries to record the same; and

e)	The Municipal Accountant reclassify the completed infrastructure project amounting to P7.275 million from the CIP account to the Road Networks account in the books of the Trust Fund, transfer to the General Fund, and subject the same to depreciation. Further, the Municipal Accountant prepare adjusting entries to record the depreciation incurred for CY 2021.

